(1871, 1, '2014-02-04 22:25:58', '2014-02-04 22:25:58', '<strong><span class="cinzel" style="font-size: 25px;">Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart (Hart)</span></strong>\r\n<strong><span class="cinzel" style="font-size: 25px;">Executive Partner</span></strong>\r\n\r\nSofiri is the commercial specialist. He advises clients on their competitiveness in the Nigerian market place. Sofiri provides each client with a tailored market entry assessment, a more specific sector review and develops strategies to help navigate risks and potential cross-sector disruptions. His intelligence on the Nigerian marketplace has come from 7 years experience in corporate Nigeria, with a leading investment bank, commercial bank, the finance ministry of an oil-producing state and a public-private partnership firm in the real estate sector. Collectively, he has gained experience on M&amp;A and financial advisory services, including: corporate finance, restructuring and reorganizations, private placements and public offerings of equity and debt securities. In 2012, Sofiri played an instrumental role structuring NGN100billion (USD$50million) government bonds created by the Rivers State Government. He also helped to secure regulatory authorizations and legal clearances (required at the bond pre-issue stage) from the Nigerian Securities and Exchange Commission.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<b>Professional experience</b>\r\n- Shutterfly Inc., Redwood City, CA, United States of America, 2015–\r\n- Government of Rivers State, Ministry of Finance, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2011–2014\r\n- Rainbow World Development Limited, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2010 – 2011\r\n- Constant Capital Partners, Lagos, Nigeria, 2008–2010\r\n- Access Bank, Lagos, Nigeria, 2006–2007\r\n\r\n<b>Professional qualification</b>\r\nAdmitted as Barrister and Solicitor, Supreme Court of Nigeria, 2008\r\n\r\n<b>Academic qualifications</b>\r\n- MBA, Darden School of Business, University of Virginia, United States of America, 2014-2016\r\n- BL, Barrister-at-Law, The Nigerian Law School, Abuja &amp; Lagos, Nigeria, 2007–2008\r\n- MSc, Master of Finance &amp; Financial Law, SOAS, University Of London, United Kingdom, 2005–2006\r\n- LLB, Bachelor of Laws, University of Reading, United Kingdom, 2002 – 2005\r\n\r\n<b>Trivia</b>\r\nIn the firm, Sofiri supports our efforts to build relationships with prospective clients, particularly within Nigeria. He also maintains close ties with a robust network of professionals in Silicon Valley to advise on potential Nigerian market entries.\r\n\r\nOutside of the firm, Sofiri enjoys photography, travelling and cooking—with a particular appreciation of Nigerian cuisine.\r\n\r\n<b>Languages</b>\r\nEnglish (Mother tongue) Igbo (Basic)', 'Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'harry-hoe', '', '', '2015-10-17 21:11:24', '2015-10-17 21:11:24', '', 0, 'http://rttheme18.demo-rt.com/?post_type=staff&#038;p=1871', 0, 'staff', '', 0),
(1872, 1, '2014-02-04 22:27:45', '2014-02-04 22:27:45', '<strong><span class="cinzel" style="font-size: 25px;">Daniel Akinmade Emejulu</span></strong>\r\n<strong><span class="cinzel" style="font-size: 25px;">Managing Partner</span></strong>\r\n\r\nDaniel is the multi-stakeholder specialist. He advises clients on their corporate citizenship in Nigeria. Daniel provides strategies to build each client’s responsible business partnerships in Nigeria—with agents of government, business and civil society. His insights on corporate citizenship and the multi-stakeholder approach have been polished at the world’s foremost institution for public-private collaboration: The World Economic Forum. He also gained cross-sector experiences in settings such as the United Nations Office in Vienna, the Red Cross in Nigeria, Simmons &amp; Simmons in London, and government ministries in both Nigeria and the UK. In 2014, Daniel led a WEF publication for global executives to catalyze private sector involvement in the Ebola response effort, which featured interviews with the Presidents of Liberia, Sierra Leone, Mali and Paul G. Allen who had donated $100million to the response effort.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<span style="font-weight: bold;">Professional experience</span>\r\n- The World Economic Forum, Geneva, Switzerland, 2013 –\r\n- Law Office of David Umar (Nigerian Senator from Niger State), Abuja, Nigeria, 2011\r\n- Simmons &amp; Simmons LLP, London, United Kingdom, 2008\r\n\r\n<b>Professional qualification</b>\r\nAdmitted as Barrister and Solicitor, Supreme Court of Nigeria, 2012 (February)\r\n\r\n<b>Academic qualifications</b>\r\n- BL, Barrister-at-Law, The Nigerian Law School, Abuja, Nigeria, 2010 – 2011\r\n- LLM, Master of Laws, Duke University, NC, United States of America, 2008 – 2009\r\n- LLB, Bachelor of Laws, SOAS, University of London, United Kingdom, 2005 – 2008\r\n\r\n<b>Trivia</b>\r\nIn the firm, Daniel acts as Managing Partner with responsibility for overall coordination of the firm. He also leads our efforts to build relationships with prospective clients outside of Nigeria, and created the Millennial Lawyers Club.\r\n\r\nOutside of the firm, Daniel enjoys writing stories, occasional acting and amateur skiing. D’Banj, Lagbaja, Asa and Wizkid are his favorite living Nigerian musicians.\r\n\r\n<b>Languages</b>\r\nEnglish (Mother tongue) French (Conversational) Yoruba (Basic)', 'Daniel Akinmade Emejulu', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'frank-foe', '', '', '2016-11-02 20:21:10', '2016-11-02 20:21:10', '', 0, 'http://rttheme18.demo-rt.com/?post_type=staff&#038;p=1872', 0, 'staff', '', 0),
