(2815, 1, '2015-09-14 12:33:06', '2015-09-14 12:33:06', '<span style="font-size: 25px;">Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart (Hart)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 25px;">Executive Partner</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Sofiri is the commercial specialist. He advises clients on their competitiveness in the Nigerian market place. Sofiri provides each client with a tailored market entry assessment, a more specific sector review and develops strategies to help navigate risks and potential cross-sector disruptions. His intelligence on the Nigerian marketplace has come from 7 years experience in corporate Nigeria, with a leading investment bank, commercial bank, the finance ministry of an oil-producing state and a public-private partnership firm in the real estate sector. Collectively, he has gained experience on </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">M&amp;A and </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">f</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">inancial advisory services, including: corporate finance, restructuring and reorganizations, private placements and public offerings of equity and debt securities</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">. In 2012, Sofiri played an instrumental role structuring NGN100billion (USD$50million) government bonds created by the Rivers State Government. He also helped to secure regulatory authorizations and legal clearances (required at the bond pre-issue stage) from the Nigerian Securities and Exchange Commission.  </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Professional experience</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Shutterfly Inc., Redwood City, CA, United States of America, 2015 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Government of Rivers State, Ministry of Finance, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2011 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2014</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rainbow World Development Limited, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2010 – 2011</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Constant Capital Partners, Lagos, Nigeria, 2008 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2010</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Access Bank, Lagos, Nigeria, 2006 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2007</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Professional qualification</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Admitted as Barrister and Solicitor, Supreme Court of Nigeria, 2008</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Academic qualifications</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">MBA, Darden School of Business, University of Virginia, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">United States of America,</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2014 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">– </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">2016</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">BL, Barrister-at-Law, The Nigerian Law School, Abuja &amp; Lagos, Nigeria, 2007 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2008</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">MSc, Master of Finance &amp; Financial Law, SOAS, University Of London, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, 2005 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2006</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">LLB, Bachelor of Laws, University of Reading, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, 2002 – 2005</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Trivia</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the firm, Sofiri supports our efforts to build relationships with prospective clients, particularly within Nigeria. He also maintains close ties with a robust network of professionals in Silicon Valley to advise on potential Nigerian market entries.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Outside of the firm, Sofiri enjoys photography, travelling and cooking—with a particular appreciation of Nigerian cuisine. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Languages</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">English (Mother tongue) Igbo (Basic)</span>', 'Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1871-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 12:33:06', '2015-09-14 12:33:06', '', 1871, 'http://www.danielhartdayo.com/2015/09/14/1871-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
