bow World Development Limited, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2010 – 2011</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Constant Capital Partners, Lagos, Nigeria, 2008 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2010</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Access Bank, Lagos, Nigeria, 2006 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2007</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Professional qualification</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Admitted as Barrister and Solicitor, Supreme Court of Nigeria, 2008</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Academic qualifications</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">MBA, Darden School of Business, University of Virginia, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">United States of America,</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2014 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">– </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">2016</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">BL, Barrister-at-Law, The Nigerian Law School, Abuja &amp; Lagos, Nigeria, 2007 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2008</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">MSc, Master of Finance &amp; Financial Law, SOAS, University Of London, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, 2005 </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">–</span><span style="font-weight: 400;"> 2006</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">LLB, Bachelor of Laws, University of Reading, </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">United Kingdom</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">, 2002 – 2005</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Trivia</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the firm, Sofiri supports our efforts to build relationships with prospective clients, particularly within Nigeria. He also maintains close ties with a robust network of professionals in Silicon Valley to advise on potential Nigerian market entries.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Outside of the firm, Sofiri enjoys photography, travelling and cooking—with a particular appreciation of Nigerian cuisine. </span>\r\n\r\n<b>Languages</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">English (Mother tongue) Igbo (Basic)</span>', 'Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1871-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 12:35:23', '2015-09-14 12:35:23', '', 1871, 'http://www.danielhartdayo.com/2015/09/14/1871-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2817, 1, '2015-09-14 12:36:07', '2015-09-14 12:36:07', '<strong><span style="font-size: 25px;">Daniel Akinmade Emejulu</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style="font-size: 25px;">Managing Partner</span></strong>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Daniel is the multi-stakeholder specialist. He advises clients on their corporate citizenship in Nigeria. Daniel provides strategies to build each client’s responsible business partnerships in Nigeria—with agents of government, business and civil society. His insights on corporate citizenship and the multi-stakeholder approach have been polished at the world’s foremost institution for public-private collaboration: The World Economic Forum. He also gained cross-sector experiences in settings such as the United Nations Office in Vienna, the Red Cross in Nigeria, Simmons &amp; Simmons in London, and government ministries in both Nigeria and the UK. In 2014, Daniel led a WEF publication for global executives to catalyze private sector involvement in the Ebola response effort, which featured interviews with the Presidents of Liberia, Sierra Leone, Mali and Paul G. Allen who had donated $100million to the response effort.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Professional experience</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">World Economic Forum, Geneva, Switzerland, 2013 –</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Law Office of David Umar (Nigerian Senator from Niger State), Abuja, Nigeria, 2011</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Simmons &amp; Simmons LLP, London, United Kingdom, 2008</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Professional qualification</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Admitted as Barrister and Solicitor, Supreme Court of Nigeria, 2012 (February)</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Academic qualifications</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">BL, Barrister-at-Law, The Nigerian Law School, Abuja, Nigeria, 2010 – 2011</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">LLM, Master of Laws, Duke University, NC, United States of America, 2008 – 2009</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">LLB, Bachelor of Laws, SOAS, University of London, United Kingdom, 2005 – 2008</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Trivia</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">In the firm, Daniel acts as Managing Partner with responsibility for overall coordination of the firm. He also leads our efforts to build relationships with prospective clients outside of Nigeria, and created the Millennial Lawyers Club.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Outside of the firm, Daniel enjoys writing stories, occasional acting and amateur skiing. D’Banj, Lagbaja, Asa and Wizkid are his favorite living Nigerian musicians.</span>\r\n\r\n<b>Languages</b>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">English (Mother tongue) French (Conversational) Yoruba (Basic)</span>', 'Daniel Akinmade Emejulu', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1872-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-14 12:36:07', '2015-09-14 12:36:07', '', 1872, 'http://www.danielhartdayo.com/2015/09/14/1872-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
