(2984, 1, '2015-10-17 21:08:26', '2015-10-17 21:08:26', '<strong><span class="cinzel" style="font-size: 25px;">Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart (Hart)</span></strong>\r\n<strong><span class="cinzel" style="font-size: 25px;">Executive Partner</span></strong>\r\n\r\nSofiri is the commercial specialist. He advises clients on their competitiveness in the Nigerian market place. Sofiri provides each client with a tailored market entry assessment, a more specific sector review and develops strategies to help navigate risks and potential cross-sector disruptions. His intelligence on the Nigerian marketplace has come from 7 years experience in corporate Nigeria, with a leading investment bank, commercial bank, the finance ministry of an oil-producing state and a public-private partnership firm in the real estate sector. Collectively, he has gained experience on M&amp;A and financial advisory services, including: corporate finance, restructuring and reorganizations, private placements and public offerings of equity and debt securities. In 2012, Sofiri played an instrumental role structuring NGN100billion (USD$50million) government bonds created by the Rivers State Government. He also helped to secure regulatory authorizations and legal clearances (required at the bond pre-issue stage) from the Nigerian Securities and Exchange Commission.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<b>Professional experience</b>\r\n- Shutterfly Inc., Redwood City, CA, United States of America, 2015–\r\n- Government of Rivers State, Ministry of Finance, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2011–2014\r\n- Rainbow World Development Limited, Port-Harcourt, Nigeria, 2010 – 2011\r\n- Constant Capital Partners, Lagos, Nigeria, 2008–2010\r\n- Access Bank, Lagos, Nigeria, 2006–2007\r\n\r\n<b>Professional qualification</b>\r\nAdmitted as Barrister and Solicitor, Supreme Court of Nigeria, 2008\r\n\r\n<b>Academic qualifications</b>\r\n- MBA, Darden School of Business, University of Virginia, United States of America, 2014-2016\r\n- BL, Barrister-at-Law, The Nigerian Law School, Abuja &amp; Lagos, Nigeria, 2007–2008\r\n- MSc, Master of Finance &amp; Financial Law, SOAS, University Of London, United Kingdom, 2005–2006\r\n- LLB, Bachelor of Laws, University of Reading, United Kingdom, 2002 – 2005\r\n\r\n<b>Trivia</b>\r\nIn the firm, Sofiri supports our efforts to build relationships with prospective clients, particularly within Nigeria. He also maintains close ties with a robust network of professionals in Silicon Valley to advise on potential Nigerian market entries.\r\n\r\nOutside of the firm, Sofiri enjoys photography, travelling and cooking—with a particular appreciation of Nigerian cuisine.\r\n\r\n<b>Languages</b>\r\nEnglish (Mother tongue) Igbo (Basic)', 'Sofiri Ezekiel-Hart', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1871-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-10-17 21:08:26', '2015-10-17 21:08:26', '', 1871, 'http://www.danielhartdayo.com/2015/10/17/1871-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
